                                                                                <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>9</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13618574" author="lhofhansl" created="Mon, 1 Apr 2013 03:19:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What do mean with &quot;cache&quot; in this context?&lt;br/&gt;
I first thought you meant the block cache, but then I saw that &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6469&quot; title=&quot;Failure on enable/disable table will cause table state in zk to be left as enabling/disabling until master is restarted&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6469&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6469&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is linked to this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13618577" author="jxiang" created="Mon, 1 Apr 2013 03:29:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not block cache, &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; I meant the cached information like ZKTable states, sometimes, configuration as well, for example, a coprocessor is removed/added.  This may be useful for semi-dynamical configuration changes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13618986" author="ndimiduk" created="Mon, 1 Apr 2013 18:08:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This sounds like an anti-fix to me. Instead, change updates should be propagated correctly. Isn&apos;t this kind of thing what ZK watches are designed to support?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13619008" author="jxiang" created="Mon, 1 Apr 2013 18:24:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ZK watcher is an alternative. But we don&apos;t want too many ZK watchers, which may have performance impact.&lt;br/&gt;
For the ZKTable state specific, the cache should match the znode all the time since the updates are expected to from the code, not from zkcli. So generally, a ZK watcher is not needed.  If we have a watcher just for this scenario (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6469&quot; title=&quot;Failure on enable/disable table will cause table state in zk to be left as enabling/disabling until master is restarted&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6469&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6469&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), it may be a waste.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13619014" author="ndimiduk" created="Mon, 1 Apr 2013 18:28:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Isn&apos;t this resolved by the state consolidation proposed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sershe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sershe&quot;&gt;Sergey Shelukhin&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7305&quot; title=&quot;ZK based Read/Write locks for table operations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7305&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7305&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13619021" author="jxiang" created="Mon, 1 Apr 2013 18:34:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Most likely not yet. Otherwise, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6469&quot; title=&quot;Failure on enable/disable table will cause table state in zk to be left as enabling/disabling until master is restarted&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6469&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6469&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; should be closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13619032" author="ndimiduk" created="Mon, 1 Apr 2013 18:40:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No implemented, just proposed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13619494" author="ram_krish" created="Tue, 2 Apr 2013 03:52:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated the title so that this ZKTable cache is not confused with Block Cache.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14097586" author="octo47" created="Thu, 14 Aug 2014 20:24:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Upon completion of this jira &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7767&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7767&lt;/a&gt; can will not needed.&lt;br/&gt;
System table, holding table states, will be collocated with master, hope we don&apos;t need to cache anything &lt;br/&gt;
due of no network operations.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14134278" author="octo47" created="Mon, 15 Sep 2014 18:38:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7767&quot; title=&quot;Get rid of ZKTable, and table enable/disable state in ZK &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7767&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-7767&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; done, do we need this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
